            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C.) In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi dei aeterni. <persName
                            ref="#people/9" key="#Emperor/king">Hlotharius</persName> divina
                        ordinante providentia <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus.
                        Dignum est, ut imperialis dignitas tanto studiosius coniunctorum obaudiat
                        petitionem, quanto magis cognoscat ad obsequium divinae magestatis
                        pertinere. Igitur cunctorum fidelium sanctae dei ecclesiae nostrorumque
                        cognoscat sollertia, quia dilecta <rs key="#marriage">coniunx</rs> nostra
                            <persName ref="#people/10" key="#marriage">Hirmingardis</persName>
                        nostram petiit pietatem, ut pro emolumento mercedis nostre et remedium
                        animae <rs key="#siblingOf">fratris</rs> sui puerili aetate ab hac luce
                        delatum, <persName ref="#people/3933" key="#siblingOf">Hugonis</persName>
                        nomine, ad concinnanda luminaria in <rs key="#Churches">basilica</rs> beati
                        confessoris Christi <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/95"
                            key="#Allocation_to_churches #Churches">Ambrosii</orgName>, ubi ipse
                        corpore humatus requiescit, pro cuius veneratione ibidem ipse puerulus
                        sepultus est, quandam conferremus <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> ex fisco
                        nostro super ripam laci Comacini vocatam <geogName ref="#estates/260"
                            key="#Rivers #Curtes #Demesnes #Cereals #Oil #Hay/fodder #Wood #Animals #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Coloni/tenants #Churches"
                                ><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/573">Limuntam</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Demesnes">casis indominicatis</rs> et <rs key="#Churches"
                            >capella</rs> in honore <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/3511"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >sancti Genesii</orgName> et aliis aedificiis ad se pertinentibus, cum
                            <rs key="#Coloni/tenants">familiis</rs> ibidem aspicientibus, quorum
                        haec sunt nomina: <persName key="#Coloni/tenants #marriage #parentOf #siblingOf"
                                ><name ref="Urso">Ursonem</name></persName> cum <rs key="#marriage"
                            >muliere</rs> et <rs key="#childOf">infantibus</rs> suis quinque,
                        <persName key="#Coloni/tenants #marriage #parentOf #siblingOf"><name
                                ref="Rosculus">Rosculum</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#siblingOf">germano</rs> eius cum muliere et infantibus suis
                        quinque, <persName key="#Coloni/tenants #parentOf #siblingOf"><name ref="Iobianus"
                                >Iobianum</name></persName> germano ipsius et infantibus suis
                        tribus, <persName key="#Coloni/tenants #marriage #parentOf"><name ref="Ariulfus"
                                >Ariulfum</name></persName> cum muliere et tribus infantibus suis,
                        <persName key="#Coloni/tenants #marriage #parentOf"><name ref="Agipertus"
                                >Agipertum</name></persName> cum muliere et uno infante, <persName
                                    key="#Coloni/tenants #marriage #parentOf"><name ref="Lupus"
                            >Lupum</name></persName> cum muliere et quattuor infantibus suis, cum
                        omnibus pecuniabus suis, quas ipsi de pertinentia eiusdem curte habent, vel
                        omnibus pertinentiis eiusdem curtis, casis videlicet et <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Oil">olivetis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cereals">campis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wood">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Animals">pascuis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Rivers">aquis aquarumve decursibus</rs> vel omnibus adiacentiis
                        seu pertinentiis suis, et alia <rs key="#Landed_possessions #Oil"
                            >olivetula</rs> in locis <placeName ref="#places/4330"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Oil #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Aucis</placeName> et <placeName ref="#places/4331"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Oil #Fiscal_property #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Conni</placeName>. Cuius petitionem iustam recolentes ob dei amorem pro
                        mercedis nostrae augmento et refrigerium anime ipsius pueri libenter
                        annuimus. Ideoque hanc nostram auctoritatem circa eundem sanctum ac
                        venerabilem locum fieri iussimus, per quam nostros successores obsecramus,
                        ut omni in tempore absque cuiuspiam contrarietate easdem res nostra
                        indulgentia solummodo in concinnanda luminaria ibidem quieto ordine
                        dimittant, nostrisque fidelibus precipimus, ut nemo quippiam inde subtrahere
                        presumat aut quamlibet inquietudinem inferre, sed omni in tempore hac nostra
                        auctoritate ibidem ad utilitatem eiusdem eclesiae quieto ordine maneat et
                        omnis redibitio eorundem rerum in ornamento luminarium ibidem deveniat
                        perhenniter mansurum. Et ut haec nostrae auctoritatis largitio pleniorem
                        obtineat vigorem et a nostris successoribus diligentius conservetur et a
                        fidelibus intemerata servetur, manu propria subter eam firmavimus et de
                        anulo nostro subter sigillari iussimus. Signum (M.) Hlotharii gloriosissimi
                        augusti. (C.) <persName ref="#people/3906" key="#Notary #Subdeacons"
                            >Dructemirus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Subdeacons">subdiaconus</rs> atque <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>
                        advicem <persName ref="#people/1235">Egilmari</persName> recognovi et
                        scripsi. Data VIII idus maias anno Christo propitio imperii domni Hlotharii
                        pii imperatoris XVIII, indictione tertia decima; actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/65"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential #Palatium"
                            >Papiae</placeName>
                        <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Function #Residential #Palatium"
                            >palatio regio</rs>; in dei nomine feliciter amen.</ab>
